cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.IR. 

The paper deals with object detection and tracking in videos, which is a common problem in computer vision (cs.CV). The approach is semi-supervised, which involves machine learning techniques (cs.LG) and the use of criteria for reliable object detection and tracking, which involves decision-making and reasoning (cs.AI). The paper also evaluates the effectiveness of the approach using metrics like quality, coverage, diversity, and relevance, which are commonly used in multimedia (cs.MM) and information retrieval (cs.IR) research.
